value.title: AOC to VP Pence: ‘It’s Congresswoman Ocasio-Cortez to you’

value.title: Judge rules Texas' Harris County can't send mail-in ballot applications to all 2.4M residents there
value.excerpt: The Texas Supreme Court ruled that Harris County cannot send ballot applications to all 2.4 million of its registered voters.

value.title: 'Is Joy Reid hoping that President Trump dies? It sure seems like it,' Curtis Houck wrote
value.excerpt: MSNBC host Joy Reid said President Trump looks like a “very sick elderly man” and was accused of hoping he dies from coronavirus.

value.excerpt: The declassification of former CIA director John Brennan's notes proves Hillary Clinton colluded with foreign entities to inject disinformation into the 2016 campaign, Sen. Tom Cotton, R-Ark., told "Fox & Friends" Wednesday.

value.title: 'Spygate' author Bongino cheers Trump declassification move while awaiting surgery
value.excerpt: Dan Bongino has lived Russiagate for nearly four years, but he learned of President Trump’s sweeping order to declassify relevant documents on the eve of an event even more serious and personal to him.

value.title: Trump says it'll be 'fast and easy' to confirm Amy Coney Barrett
value.excerpt: President Trump declared on Twitter Tuesday evening that the Senate battle to confirm Amy Coney Barrett to the Supreme Court “will be fast and easy.”

value.title: Puerto Rico Gov. Wanda Vázquez Garced endorses Trump re-election bid
value.excerpt: Last month, the Trump administration unveiled a $13 billion aid package to help Puerto Rico in its ongoing recovery from Hurricane Maria.

value.title: Biden vows not to allow ‘White supremacists to overturn the America of Lincoln’
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden made a forceful plea for national unity on Tuesday as he took aim at “extremist white supremacist groups menacing our communities.”

value.title: Biden raises eyebrows after telling 'these beautiful young ladies' he wants to 'see them dancing when they're four years older'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden has been raising eyebrows again with remarks he made to a group of "beautiful young ladies" during a campaign stop in Miami.

value.title: Pence to vote in Indiana this week as state's early voting begins
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and second lady Karen Pence are expected to fly to Indiana Friday, to vote in person from the second family’s home state, as early voting kicked off Tuesday.

value.title: Hollywood-inspired ‘Trump’ sign pops up on mountainside above California freeway
value.excerpt: A towering, Hollywood-esque Trump sign briefly appeared above California’s 405 Freeway near Sepulveda Pass, just to the west of Los Angeles, before workers took it down Tuesday.

value.title: Trump calls for pause on coronavirus stimulus talks until after the election
value.excerpt: President Trump on Tuesday said he has instructed Republicans to pause negotiations on a coronavirus stimulus package until after the election, instructing Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell, R-Ky., to focus “full-time” on getting his nominee to fill the vacant seat on the U.S. Supreme Court approved.

value.title: Phil Murphy slams Trump over New Jersey fundraiser, says event is under investigation
value.excerpt: New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy slammed President Trump for holding a high-dollar fundraiser in the state less than one day before he tested positive for COVID-19, accusing the president of needlessly exposing attendees to the virus.

value.title: Trump deploying 'high-risk strategy' by leaving hospital so early, Rollins says
value.excerpt: The president is deploying a "high-risk strategy" by leaving Walter Reed hospital earlier than expected, Republican strategist Ed Rollins told NYT.

value.title: Don’t Underestimate Mike Pence
value.excerpt: A soothing dose of Hoosier calm might be just what the Trump campaign needed.

value.title: Biden suggests people were able to quarantine because 'some Black woman was able to stack the grocery shelf' in viral clip
value.excerpt: Joe Biden has landed in hot water over a viral clip of him suggesting why people were able to quarantine during the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: Joe Biden enlists artists like Ludacris, Dupri, Jeezy and Monica for voting ads in battleground states
value.excerpt: Joe Biden has tapped popular music artists like Ludacris, Monica, Jermaine Dupri and Jeezy to encourage Black citizens in battleground states to vote in the upcoming presidential election.

value.title: Who is Dr. Sean Conley, President Trump's physician?
value.excerpt: Conley, an officer in the U.S. Navy, earned his B.S. from the University of Notre Dame in 2002, according to his LinkedIn. He earned his D.O. from the Philadelphia College of Osteopathic Medicine and is an experienced emergency physician.

value.title: Biden visits Miami's Little Havana, Haiti ahead of national town hall from key swing state of Florida
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden is expected to visit Miami’s Little Havana and Little Haiti ahead of a televised town hall Monday, as the former vice president returns to the critical swing state of Florida in the final homestretch of his election campaign.

value.title: Pence to maintain 'aggressive schedule' as Trump remains in hospital, campaign adviser says
value.excerpt: A senior Trump campaign adviser said on Sunday that Vice President Mike Pence will maintain “a very full aggressive schedule” while the president is being treated in the hospital for COVID-19.

value.title: VP Pence and second lady test negative for COVID, twice in three days
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and his wife, Karen, have against tested negative again for COVID-19 just days after President Trump and the first lady were diagnosed with the virus, White House officials confirmed to Fox News.

value.title: Trump health update expected at Walter Reed Medical Center
value.excerpt: President Trump’s medical team is expected to give an update on his health Sunday morning, as members of the White House press pool head to the Walter Reed Medical Center to be briefed on his condition.
